Types parameterised by other types. Enables generic containers without sacrificing performance.

```julia
struct Stack{T}
    data::Vector{T}
end

push!(s::Stack{T}, x::T) where T = push!(s.data, x)

s = Stack{Int}([])
push!(s, 42)  # type-safe, compiled specialisation

# Built-in examples:
Vector{Float64}  # same as Array{Float64,1}
Dict{String, Int}
```

```julia
using JuMP, HiGHS  # (requires installation)

model = Model(HiGHS.Optimizer)

@variable(model, x >= 0)
@variable(model, y >= 0)
@constraint(model, x + y <= 10)
@constraint(model, 2x + y <= 16)
@objective(model, Max, 3x + 5y)

optimize!(model)
println(value(x), value(y))  # 6, 4  → obj=38
```

MacroEnergy.jl builds large JuMP models automatically from network topology and time-series data. The `@variable`, `@constraint`, `@objective` macros create Expr objects that JuMP translates to solver matrices.

```julia
using Test

# Basic assertions
